attributes.comment:
I am curious why there are discrepancies in the time required to process certain
applications. For example, in your document requesting the fee increase, your
estimated time for completion of an I-129F is 2.9 months, but on your page listing
currently processed I-129F forms, the most recent one is almost seven months
old. Most sources I have seen give the actual processing time for this application
as being between four to eight months.

Likewise, the I-130 form takes, according to the fee increase document, around
six months. All other sources, including your own process date site, indicate a
year or more - even up to two years.

Which numbers are correct? And why are the most optimistic numbers the ones
you are using as justification for fee increases? And finally, will we see an end to
the stories I've read of how your Vermont office still files applications in milk
crates?

Thank you for the opportunity to comment on this important issue.
attributes.title: Comment Submitted By Charles Hesse
